rComments: Prof. Dong's exams are delightful (very fair, not tricky)!  But her powerpoints can be confusing if you didn't  glance over the course material.  If you peruse the book before, go to class, and do the occasional homework problem, you should be fine.  I'm no chemistry genius but her class made it pretty easy easy to succeed.
Such a good prof.  Everything makes so much sense and is so much fun.  And to top it all off she's hot too.
Lectures in a clear and concise manner. She makes learning organic chemistry...fun!
Sweet, helpful, enthusiastic. Barely needed to refer to text for her section of the course.
Awesome!  We miss her A LOT.
